Let me review the Solution.java code you provided:
Overall the code looks good and implements a set associative cache with LRU and MRU replacement algorithms. Here are a few things I noticed:
- The CacheSet linked list implementation for tracking LRU/MRU order looks good.
- The IReplacementAlgo interface is defined, and LRU/MRU algorithms implement it properly.
- The SetAssociativeCache implements the core cache logic and makes use of the CacheSet and IReplacementAlgo abstractions nicely.
- The helper/factory classes at the bottom look good for enabling test case execution.
A few minor improvements that could be made:
- Add some comments explaining the overall flow and key parts of the cache logic.
- The CacheItem class could be made more immutable by removing setters and making fields final.
- Validate arguments in constructors and methods to fail fast on invalid values.
- Use generics more extensively to avoid casting.
But overall the implementation looks solid. I don't see any major issues that would prevent it from passing test cases and meeting the requirements. Let me know if you have any other specific concerns!
